{
  "id": {
    "address": "deepbook",
    "name": "ewma"
  },
  "doc": " The Exponentially Weighted Moving Average (EWMA) state for DeepBook\n This state is used to calculate the smoothed mean and variance of gas prices\n and apply a penalty to taker fees based on the Z-score of the current gas price\n relative to the smoothed mean and variance.\n The state is disabled by default and can be configured with different parameters.",
